FOOT AND MOUTH DISEASE IN GEORGIA (CLINICAL DIAGNOSIS)
-----------------------------------------------
Information received on 31 March 2004 from Dr Levan Ramishvili, Head of the
Veterinary Department, Ministry of Agriculture and Food, Tbilisi:
Date of the report: 31 Mar 2004.
One outbreak of foot and mouth disease was clinically diagnosed in Kaspi
district, Doesi village (in the central part of the country).
Date of initial detection of animal health incident: 29 Mar 2004.
Estimated date of primary infection: 20 Mar 2004.
Description of affected population: cattle of local breed (private farm).
Total number of cases: 12 (8 cows and 4 calves).
Control measures:
- vaccination ;
- quarantine ;
- movement control inside the country.
--
